  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-10 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are fully assessed; each achievedLevel meets or exceeds the requiredLevel. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is documented. Decision: Accepted. This package is a negative-control synthetic sample (NC-10): no Critical or High weakeners co-exist; no compound triggers should fire.",
