        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "SQA acceptance criteria — MRL 5 CFD solver",
        "description": "CFD solver must be under formal configuration management, with documented version control, regression test suite covering at least 95% of relevant physics modules, and traceable issue-resolution records. All solver modifications since last validated release must be documented and reviewed."
      },
      "rationale": "OpenFOAM v9 is deployed under Git-based configuration management with a documented 312-case regression suite. All physics-module changes since v8 are logged in a formal change-control register reviewed by two independent engineers. Achieved Gradation 4 confirmed by third-party SQA audit completed 2025-11."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-ncv",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-ncv",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical code verification acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Solver must demonstrate second-order spatial convergence on manufactured solutions for incompressible Navier-Stokes and scalar transport (hemolysis surrogate). Order-of-accuracy must be confirmed on at least three systematically refined grids with L2 error norms reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Method-of-manufactured-solutions (MMS) verification confirmed second-order spatial accuracy (L2 norm) for velocity, pressure, and hemolysis scalar on four grid levels (h, h/2, h/4, h/8). Observed orders of accuracy: 1.97 (velocity), 2.01 (pressure), 1.94 (hemolysis scalar). Exceeds Gradation 4 threshold; Gradation 5 awarded."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-de",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-de",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for the hemolysis index QoI using at least three systematically refined meshes. GCI on the fine grid must be below 5% for the primary hemolysis QoI. Time-step convergence study required for transient impeller rotation."
      },
      "rationale": "Richardson extrapolation and GCI analysis performed on three meshes (4.2M, 12.6M, 37.8M cells). Fine-grid GCI for hemolysis index: 3.1%. Time-step refinement study (dt = 1e-4, 5e-5, 2.5e-5 s) shows < 1.5% variation in hemolysis index. Discretization error budget is within acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-tc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-tc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test conditions acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, temperature) must be measured with calibrated instrumentation and reported with uncertainty bounds. CFD boundary conditions must be set to match experimental values within measurement uncertainty."
      },
      "rationale": "NIB experimental campaign used calibrated Coriolis flow meters (±0.3% FS) and torque transducers (±0.1% FS). Fluid temperature controlled to 37±0.5°C; bovine blood viscosity characterised by cone-and-plate rheometry. All five operating points (Q=3–8 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM) reproduced in CFD with boundary conditions set to measured mean values."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-oc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-oc",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Predicted hemolysis index (normalised index of hemolysis, NIH) must agree with experimental measurements within combined simulation and experimental uncertainty at all five operating points. Agreement metric: |E_rel| ≤ 15% at each point, with mean absolute error ≤ 10%."
      },
      "rationale": "Comparison of CFD-predicted NIH against NIB experimental data across five operating points: mean absolute relative error = 7.3%; maximum absolute relative error = 13.8% (at Q=8 L/min, 3600 RPM). All five points satisfy the ≤15% per-point criterion; mean satisfies ≤10% criterion. Combined uncertainty bands overlap at all points."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-rqi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-rqi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "QoI relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The primary QoI (normalised index of hemolysis) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (patient hemolysis risk). The hemolysis power-law model must be identified and justified as the appropriate damage accumulation model for the operating regime."
      },
      "rationale": "NIH is the FDA-recognised metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment and directly maps to clinical hemolysis risk. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model is applied with Lagrangian particle tracking; model applicability to the shear-stress and exposure-time ranges in this pump has been documented in peer-reviewed literature (Goubergrits 2004, Fraser 2012). QoI is fully relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-rva",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-rva",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Validation activity relevance acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry (FDA generic centrifugal pump), the same fluid (bovine blood or validated blood analogue), and operating conditions spanning the COU envelope. Validation data must not have been used for model calibration."
      },
      "rationale": "Validation uses the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry (identical to COU geometry) with bovine blood at physiological conditions. Operating envelope (Q=3–8 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM) spans the full COU envelope. NIB experimental dataset is independent of any model calibration activities; data partition documented in data management plan."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-nse",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-nse",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Iterative convergence of residuals must reach at least 1e-5 for all transport equations at each time step. Mass imbalance must be below 0.01% of inlet mass flow. Floating-point precision must be double throughout."
      },
      "rationale": "All simulations run in double precision. Residual convergence to 1e-6 achieved within 200 inner iterations per time step for all equations. Mass imbalance < 0.005% of inlet mass flow at all operating points. Solver error contribution to hemolysis index uncertainty estimated at < 0.5% by perturbation analysis."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-ue",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-ue",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Use error acceptance criteria",
        "description": "A documented simulation plan must be followed by trained analysts. An independent peer review of simulation setup (mesh, boundary conditions, solver settings, post-processing scripts) must be completed prior to results being used for regulatory submission."
      },
      "rationale": "Simulation plan (SP-COU2-v2.1) was authored and followed by two CFD engineers with > 5 years of blood pump CFD experience. Independent peer review of all setup files and post-processing scripts completed by external reviewer (not involved in model development). Review findings resolved and documented in review record RR-COU2-2025-09."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-mf",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-mf",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The turbulence model must be justified for the flow regime (transitional/turbulent, Re ~ 1e4–1e5). Sensitivity of hemolysis predictions to turbulence model choice must be quantified. The hemolysis damage model must be justified for the shear-stress and exposure-time ranges present in the pump."
      },
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model selected based on documented performance for confined rotating flows in blood pumps (Hariharan 2011, Pauli 2014). Turbulence model sensitivity study compared SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and LES on the 12.6M mesh; hemolysis index varied by ±8% across models, within the combined uncertainty budget. Hemolysis power-law model applicability confirmed for shear stress range 1–600 Pa and exposure times 1–500 ms present in this pump."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-mi",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-mi",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model inputs acceptance criteria",
        "description": "All uncertain model inputs (blood viscosity, hemolysis power-law coefficients, inlet velocity profile) must be characterised with probability distributions and propagated through the model via Monte Carlo analysis. At least 500 Monte Carlo samples required. 95% prediction interval for hemolysis index must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification performed with 1000 Latin-hypercube samples propagating uncertainty in: blood viscosity (log-normal, CV=8%), hemolysis power-law exponent α (normal, ±5%), hemolysis power-law coefficient C (log-normal, CV=12%), inlet turbulence intensity (uniform, 3–8%). 95% prediction interval for NIH at each operating point computed and reported in UQ report UQR-COU2-2025-10. All inputs characterised from literature and experimental data."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-ts",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-ts",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Test samples acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Experimental hemolysis measurements must be performed with at least three independent blood samples per operating point to characterise biological variability. Sample-to-sample coefficient of variation must be reported."
      },
      "rationale": "NIB experimental protocol used four independent bovine blood draws per operating point (n=4 per point, 20 total). Inter-sample CV for NIH ranged from 4.2% to 9.7% across operating points, consistent with published biological variability for bovine blood hemolysis assays. Sample variability incorporated into combined uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cf/cou2-eip",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/cou2-eip",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "The geometric fidelity of the CFD model relative to the physical test article must be documented. Any differences in fluid properties between validation experiments (bovine blood) and COU (human blood) must be assessed and their impact on hemolysis predictions quantified."
      },
      "rationale": "CFD geometry derived from FDA-published STL file; dimensional verification against physical pump confirmed deviations < 0.05 mm on all critical features (impeller tip clearance, volute throat). Bovine-to-human blood equivalency assessed via rheological comparison: viscosity ratio at 37°C within 6%; hemolysis susceptibility scaling factor applied per published protocol (Taskin 2012). Equivalency impact on NIH estimated at < 5%, within uncertainty budget."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou2-accepted-2026-04",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-vv40-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and all achievedLevels meet or exceed the corresponding requiredLevels for Model Risk Level 5. Software quality assurance, numerical code verification, discretization error, test conditions, output comparison, QoI relevance, validation activity relevance, model form, model inputs, and equivalency of input parameters are each assessed at Gradation 4 or above. Numerical solver error, use error, and test samples are assessed at Gradation 3, consistent with MRL 5 requirements for these factors. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (1000 LHS samples) has been completed and 95% prediction intervals for the hemolysis index are within the clinical acceptance threshold at all five operating points. Mean absolute relative error against NIB experimental data is 7.3%, satisfying the ≤10% acceptance criterion. Combined simulation and experimental uncertainty bands overlap at all operating points. Independent peer review of simulation setup and post-processing has been completed and documented. On the basis of the structured credibility evidence, the model is accepted for predicting absolute hemolysis levels for the Class III VAD COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
